55
00:02:19,536 --> 00:02:23,552
Just make sure you've marked
July 27th on your calendar.

56
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,800
你只需要确保你能记住7月27号这一天

57
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,600
毫无疑问
Abso-bloody-lutely!

58
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,700
Phoebe 说谢谢 
Say thank you, Phoebe.

59
00:02:33,512 --> 00:02:37,516
She's highly strung. V creative.

60
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,500
她一直神经紧绷

61
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,400
非常有创造力

62
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,400
噢 上帝会保佑她的
Oh, bless her.

63
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,900
如何

64
00:02:45,512 --> 00:02:49,584
How'd it go? Like taking candy
from a baby. Ah-ha.

65
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:49,000
- 轻而易举
- 啊哈

66
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:52,200
真有趣 你总是会特别钟情于某些工作
It's funny how you enjoy some jobs
more than others.

67
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:54,600
那是这些人值得拥有
Some people are more deserving
than others.

68
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:58,100
- 所以干得更带劲
- 嗯 的确如此 
Makes it all the sweeter.
Yes, it does. Mind you...

69
00:02:57,536 --> 00:03:01,540
A hundred grand ain't to be sniffed
at. No. It's a lot of clothes.

70
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,600
主意 10万英镑可不容小觑

71
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,300
的确不容忽视 
可以买很多衣服呢

72
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:03,900
实话说 反正他们钱多
To tell you the truth,
they had way too much money anyway.

73
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,800
仔细想想 我们跟侠盗罗宾汉有点儿像

74
00:03:04,536 --> 00:03:07,512
I mean, when you think about it,
we're a bit like Robin Hood.

75
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,600
是啊 我们确实从富人那儿弄钱

76
00:03:07,512 --> 00:03:08,596
Yeah, well,
we do take from the rich...

77
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,500
- 只不过不捐给穷人
- 我们拿来买衣服
Only instead of giving it
to the poor... We buy clothes.

78
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,700
- 还是挺低调的
- 的确
